## AI development workflow

- Tier 0: docs, comments, copy, or non-logic style changes. Make minimal changes and verify as needed.
- Tier 1: low-risk single-file bugs outside API/data/auth/external/legacy boundaries. Diagnose briefly, fix minimally, run focused verification.
- Tier 2: API, data contract, DTO/VO, frontend type, repository/mapper, query, or response-shape changes. Analyze impact and verify both sides of the contract.
- Tier 3: dangerous modules, external systems, state machines, migrations, legacy/compatibility layers, auth/security, or high-coupling areas. Analyze first, produce a plan, require human confirmation when listed below, then verify.

